longer than you have.

528
00:31:28,219 --> 00:31:31,996
You think about Jenna all the time.

529
00:31:32,290 --> 00:31:37,694
Why don't you go back
and make it right?

530
00:31:37,695 --> 00:31:41,142
It's, it's complicated, Dad.

531
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:44,201
It's just better this way.

532
00:31:44,202 --> 00:31:47,706
You mean, it's easier for you this way?

533
00:31:49,307 --> 00:31:51,309
You don't understand.

534
00:31:51,442 --> 00:31:53,277
Of course not. I've told you,

535
00:31:53,278 --> 00:31:55,746
love is a mystery to me.

536
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:57,481
And any person who claims to

537
00:31:57,482 --> 00:31:59,883
fully understand what
draws 2 people together

538
00:31:59,884 --> 00:32:03,297
is either a blithering fool

539
00:32:03,488 --> 00:32:05,255
or an advertiser trying to sell jewelry.

540
00:32:05,256 --> 00:32:08,066
But one thing I do know,

541
00:32:08,426 --> 00:32:14,103
if you are fortunate enough
to meet someone,

542
00:32:14,198 --> 00:32:18,302
anyone you can share time with,

543
00:32:18,303 --> 00:32:24,617
for however much time
you may have left,

544
00:32:25,810 --> 00:32:31,020
you are an absolute fool
if you let that time slip by.

545
00:32:31,516 --> 00:32:34,851
Yeah, well, the fact is,
our time is up.

546
00:32:34,852 --> 00:32:38,060
There's not a damn thing
anyone can do about it.

547
00:32:38,790 --> 00:32:40,057
Look.

548
00:32:40,058 --> 00:32:41,625
Don't worry about going back to town.

549
00:32:41,626 --> 00:32:45,403
Forget the tomatoes.
I'll, I'll get some beets.

550
00:33:06,818 --> 00:33:09,486
You want me to push everyone away,
retreat from the world,

551
00:33:09,487 --> 00:33:11,888
and be alone like you?

552
00:33:11,889 --> 00:33:13,557
What are you frightened of?

553
00:33:13,558 --> 00:33:15,192
Dad, I'm not frightened.

554
00:33:15,193 --> 00:33:16,960
I've been expecting this for a while.

555
00:33:16,961 --> 00:33:18,997
Expecting what?

556
00:33:19,564 --> 00:33:22,135
Answers, David.

557
00:33:22,433 --> 00:33:25,470
You'd better fill me in
if you don't want me to go into town.

558
00:33:26,004 --> 00:33:27,771
I presume this is not
just about my attempts

559
00:33:27,772 --> 00:33:30,173
to pursue a romance
at the local restaurant.

560
00:33:30,174 --> 00:33:32,347
No, of course it's not.

561
00:33:32,744 --> 00:33:38,815
Well then, I must assume
this is to do with your other concern.

562
00:33:38,816 --> 00:33:40,384
Oh, what's that?

563
00:33:40,385 --> 00:33:42,887
Those polar bear fields, right?

564
00:33:43,388 --> 00:33:45,697
Polar bear fields?

565
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:48,367
I glanced at your notebook.

566
00:33:48,626 --> 00:33:52,362
Dad, those are the compass bearings

567
00:33:52,363 --> 00:33:56,572
of the, of the polar magnetic fields.

568
00:33:56,968 --> 00:33:58,970
What are you talking about?

569
00:33:59,537 --> 00:34:01,104
All right.

570
00:34:01,105 --> 00:34:03,846
Do you know how the dinosaurs died?

571
00:34:04,976 --> 00:34:06,710
Yes, they got a taste of your cooking.

572
00:34:06,711 --> 00:34:10,021
Uh, look, Dad, I'm being serious.

573
00:34:10,314 --> 00:34:11,481
There was, uh,

574
00:34:11,482 --> 00:34:14,418
there was some kind of
massive geophysical event, all right?

575
00:34:14,419 --> 00:34:16,720
Uh, uh, pro- most probably
a meteor strike.

576
00:34:16,721 --> 00:34:20,323
But, something else happened.

577
00:34:20,324 --> 00:34:25,062
The Earth's magnetic fields
were weakened by up to 80%

578
00:34:25,063 --> 00:34:28,632
That's why the dinosaurs
weren't able to re-evolve.

579
00:34:28,633 --> 00:34:32,269
There was a massive die-off
of all living things.

580
00:34:32,270 --> 00:34:33,908
Well,

581
00:34:36,874 --> 00:34:39,012
now it's our turn.

582
00:34:41,412 --> 00:34:44,181
My life's complicated enough.

583
00:34:44,182 --> 00:34:48,220
I wouldn't wish this kind of complication
on anyone I love.

584
00:34:53,424 --> 00:34:56,131
Then why the bloody hell
did you tell me?

585
00:34:57,462 --> 00:35:02,138
What do you say we have filet mignon
for supper tonight instead, huh?

586
00:35:27,859 --> 00:35:29,394
General.

587
00:35:34,799 --> 00:35:36,099
General Railen?

588
00:35:36,100 --> 00:35:37,977
Right this way, ma'am.

589
00:35:38,169 --> 00:35:39,511
Sir.

590
00:36:14,071 --> 00:36:14,871
Clinic?

591
00:36:14,872 --> 00:36:15,906
Hey, Jenna.

592
00:36:15,907 --> 00:36:18,341
This is Debbie
at the CDC returning Joe's call.

593
00:36:18,342 --> 00:36:20,210
Hey Debbie.
Do you want to talk to him?

594
00:36:20,211 --> 00:36:21,344
Oh no. Ooh, please.

595
00:36:21,345 --> 00:36:23,747
There is only so much Joe
I can take in a week.

596
00:36:23,748 --> 00:36:27,684
I would have called you on your cell,
but, satellite communications are down.

597
00:36:27,685 --> 00:36:28,818
Really?

598
00:36:28,819 --> 00:36:30,020
You didn't know?

599
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:33,023
Okay, Jenna, you really need to
watch the news more often.

600
00:36:33,024 --> 00:36:34,357
Well, we had a small earthquake here

601
00:36:34,358 --> 00:36:36,593
and the power was out
for a couple minutes, so.

602
00:36:36,594 --> 00:36:38,361
Yeah, that's been happening everywhere.

603
00:36:38,362 --> 00:36:41,031
No one knows why,
but it isn't pretty.

604
00:36:41,032 --> 00:36:42,699
Well, my brother said
something happened.

605
00:36:42,700 --> 00:36:45,602
Well, whatever it was, there's been
an overnight international rise

606
00:36:45,603 --> 00:36:48,672
in what looks like radiation sickness.

607
00:36:48,673 --> 00:36:50,507
You know, that fits, Debbie,

608
00:36:50,508 --> 00:36:53,176
because, I think I found a pattern.

609
00:36:53,177 --> 00:36:54,978
Everybody here that's
coming down with symptoms,

610
00:36:54,979 --> 00:36:57,547
they're all successful chemo
and radiation patients.

611
00:36:57,548 --> 00:37:01,051
It's like it's only hitting
the healthy ones.

612
00:37:01,052 --> 00:37:03,253
The answer is inside of them, Jenna.

613
00:37:03,254 --> 00:37:04,120
What?

614
00:37:04,121 --> 00:37:06,990
RLIP-76.

615
00:37:06,991 --> 00:37:09,125
It's a protein we've been looking at.

616
00:37:09,126 --> 00:37:10,827
It acts as a barrier to stressors

617
00:37:10,828 --> 00:37:13,663
like chemotherapeutic agents
and radiation.

618
00:37:13,664 --> 00:37:16,405
Some people have it, some don't.

619
00:37:16,434 --> 00:37:18,835
And the ones who don't
are more sensitive to radiation.

620
00:37:18,836 --> 00:37:20,670
Exactly. It's great for fighting cancer,

621
00:37:20,671 --> 00:37:24,941
but unfortunately, it leaves them
more vulnerable to other exposures.

622
00:37:24,942 --> 00:37:27,077
Listen,
try to keep your patients inside.

623
00:37:27,078 --> 00:37:29,312
We've just issued a global health alert.

624
00:37:29,313 --> 00:37:30,814
Do you have Hazmat supply?

625
00:37:30,815 --> 00:37:31,648
Yes.

626
00:37:31,649 --> 00:37:33,984
Yeah, I'm sorry it's not better news.

627
00:37:33,985 --> 00:37:36,086
But if your brother can share
any insight into this,

628
00:37:36,087 --> 00:37:38,088
could you have him call me here?

629
00:37:38,089 --> 00:37:41,224
And Jenna,
watch for symptoms in yourself.

630
00:37:41,225 --> 00:37:44,060
'Cause over 1/3 of our staff
has already been hit.

631
00:37:44,061 --> 00:37:46,666
Okay. Thanks, Debbie. Bye.

