Planet at risk.

1291
01:18:01,777 --> 01:18:03,244
She needs time to heal.

1292
01:18:03,245 --> 01:18:04,311
Al.

1293
01:18:04,312 --> 01:18:07,181
You said before you lost power,
the model was stabilizing?

1294
01:18:07,182 --> 01:18:08,149
I think so.

1295
01:18:08,150 --> 01:18:10,951
I'm, the field was chaotic
but balanced, and,

1296
01:18:10,952 --> 01:18:14,055
and rotation had stopped decelerating.

1297
01:18:14,056 --> 01:18:17,093
Come on, come on,
why is this taking so long?

1298
01:18:17,659 --> 01:18:19,627
What- who are you all talking to?

1299
01:18:19,628 --> 01:18:22,063
Oh, here it comes.
This is the President.

1300
01:18:22,064 --> 01:18:23,264
Can I meet him too?

1301
01:18:23,265 --> 01:18:23,998
Al.

1302
01:18:23,999 --> 01:18:26,400
Proceeding on McNeil's recommendation.

1303
01:18:26,401 --> 01:18:32,214
No. McNeil does not have all the facts.

1304
01:18:32,741 --> 01:18:35,983
I don't think he would care
even if he did.

1305
01:18:37,412 --> 01:18:39,146
We're losing it.

1306
01:18:39,147 --> 01:18:40,247
How much time?

1307
01:18:40,248 --> 01:18:42,227
Not enough.

1308
01:18:42,651 --> 01:18:44,994
It's fading.
-Okay, all right.

1309
01:18:45,353 --> 01:18:46,854
Here, how's that?

1310
01:18:46,855 --> 01:18:47,822
Well, it's coming through.

1311
01:18:47,823 --> 01:18:50,691
It's okay.
What, he wants to know what facts.

1312
01:18:50,692 --> 01:18:52,093
What facts?

1313
01:18:52,094 --> 01:18:54,361
We don't have all the facts ourselves.

1314
01:18:54,362 --> 01:18:57,365
Leap of faith, David.
You know the truth.

1315
01:18:59,000 --> 01:19:00,468
Yeah, General, may I?

1316
01:19:00,469 --> 01:19:01,970
Thank you.

1317
01:19:33,401 --> 01:19:34,902
Can someone read this one too?

1318
01:19:34,903 --> 01:19:37,280
I- I- I lost my glasses.

1319
01:19:54,456 --> 01:19:56,390
End target is in range.

1320
01:19:56,391 --> 01:19:57,191
Negative, Bomber One,

1321
01:19:57,192 --> 01:19:59,226
you are to abort your mission
and return to base.

1322
01:19:59,227 --> 01:20:02,129
Repeat, abort your mission
and return to base.

1323
01:20:02,130 --> 01:20:03,764
Roger that. Standing down.

1324
01:20:03,765 --> 01:20:05,505
Returning to base.

1325
01:20:20,215 --> 01:20:22,661
Bomber standing down.

1326
01:20:26,588 --> 01:20:28,189
Congratulations General.

1327
01:20:28,190 --> 01:20:30,291
Well done, well done.

1328
01:20:30,292 --> 01:20:31,827
You okay.

1329
01:20:32,527 --> 01:20:35,439
Are you okay?
-Yeah. I'm okay.

1330
01:20:39,234 --> 01:20:40,769
Hey.

1331
01:20:42,003 --> 01:20:44,915
Come on.
-Hey, how about me?

1332
01:20:45,540 --> 01:20:48,020
Yeah. We did it.
-I think so.

1333
01:20:48,176 --> 01:20:49,743
Listen, I don't know
if you all have any plans,

1334
01:20:49,744 --> 01:20:52,479
but I say we deserve a nice vacation.

1335
01:20:52,480 --> 01:20:54,584
And I know just where to go.

1336
01:21:10,332 --> 01:21:12,812
Hello.
-Hi Sweetie.

1337
01:21:20,709 --> 01:21:23,510
Ah, hello. How are you?

1338
01:21:23,511 --> 01:21:25,079
See, Ellenita.

1339
01:21:25,080 --> 01:21:27,314
She's beautiful. Ellenita?
-Sí. Ellenita, yeah.

1340
01:21:27,315 --> 01:21:31,585
Oh, she's beautiful.
-Sí. Yeah.

1341
01:21:31,586 --> 01:21:33,690
Her daughter. My daughter.

1342
01:21:34,456 --> 01:21:36,333
Bye, bye.
-Bye.

1343
01:21:45,333 --> 01:21:49,270
So, I've been working on this theory

1344
01:21:49,271 --> 01:21:52,473
about the multiple pole
anomaly stabilization

1345
01:21:52,474 --> 01:21:53,941
of the magnetosphere.

1346
01:21:53,942 --> 01:21:55,716
You have?

1347
01:21:56,077 --> 01:21:58,913
You got all your facts together already?

1348
01:21:58,914 --> 01:22:00,415
No.

1349
01:22:00,749 --> 01:22:05,391
This is more of a, uh,
gut instinct theory.

1350
01:22:06,488 --> 01:22:07,554
Really?

1351
01:22:07,555 --> 01:22:11,025
Ha. Wow. In that case I can't wait.

1352
01:22:11,026 --> 01:22:13,005
What do you got?

1353
01:22:13,862 --> 01:22:20,404
I figure maybe somebody thought
we all deserved a second chance.

1354
01:22:21,300 --> 01:22:26,300
Subtitles: Arigon

1355
01:22:26,508 --> 01:22:28,453
Yeah, I'll buy that.

1356
01:22:32,213 --> 01:22:34,248
Ah, it's really too bad
about your father, though.

1357
01:22:34,249 --> 01:22:36,490
He would have enjoyed this trip.

1358
01:22:40,188 --> 01:22:45,501
No, I rather think he's enjoying himself
right where he is.

1359
01:22:49,130 --> 01:22:52,338
Yes, I have the whole place to myself.

1360
01:22:53,868 --> 01:22:56,704
And when the sun set behind those trees,

1361
01:22:56,705 --> 01:22:58,739
it is a sight to see.

1362
01:22:58,740 --> 01:23:00,841
It's so beautiful.

1363
01:23:00,842 --> 01:23:01,775
Well, the cabin's not much,

1364
01:23:01,776 --> 01:23:04,478
but it's better than a slap in the face
with a wet kipper

1365
01:23:04,479 --> 01:23:05,813
if you know what I mean.

1366
01:23:05,814 --> 01:23:07,691
No, I don't.

1367
01:23:08,450 --> 01:23:13,421
But in physics,
one law remains the same.

1368
01:23:15,090 --> 01:23:17,627
Opposites do attract.

